Sentencas: In this paper solid oxide fuel cells operating with dry synthetic biogas have been examined.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: In order to increase their stability the layers of CuO-CeO2, Cu1.3Mn1.7O4 and Y0.08Sr0.92Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-delta have been deposited on the Ni-YSZ anode site.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: These layers should catalyze the internal biogas reforming and prevent the carbon deposition on the anode site.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: It has been found that CuO-CeO2 and Cu1.3Mn1.7O4 catalysts led to an increase of the stability (at least 7 days) of the fabricated fuel cells powered by biogas, whereas the unmodified fuel cell, as well as the fuel cell with Y0.08Sr0.92Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-delta catalyst degraded gradually with time.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: A significant amount of carbon nanofibers has been formed on the catalyst surface after fuel cell test.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: However, they have not formed in the anode area.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas

Sentencas: The use of CuO-CeO2 and Cu1.3Mn1.7O4 catalysts prevented the carbon deposition on the anode site, and thus the fuel cell degradation was slower when operating with biogas fuel.
Titulo: Investigation of catalytic layers on anode for solid oxide fuel cells operating with synthetic biogas
